benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods - Retrieve account payment methods

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval with various query parameters (TC01, TC02, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07) and default behavior without query params.
Empty Response: Scenario for account with no payment methods returns an empty array (TC08).
Query Parameters: Extensive coverage of combinations including withPluginInfo, includedDeleted, pluginProperty, and audit values (TC02-TC07, TC12, TC13).
Authorization: 401 when authentication token is missing (TC11).
Error Handling & Security: 404 for non-existent account (TC09), 400 for invalid accountId (TC10), 400 for invalid audit (TC12), SQL injection (TC17) and XSS (TC18) scenarios.
Resilience and Performance: 503 for service unavailability (TC15), 502/503 for plugin service issues (TC22), 503 retry scenario (TC19), and performance check with large datasets (TC14).
Regression/State/Accessibility: Tests for regression (TC20, TC21), partially populated DB (TC23), and screen reader accessibility (TC24).
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests asserting correct pagination semantics (page/size) or pagination headers.
Rate Limiting: No tests verifying throttling or rate-limiting behavior.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or conditional requests.
Authorization Edge Case: No test for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions (only 401 tested).
Internal Server Error: No test for 500 Internal Server Error (only 503/502 covered).
Audit NONE: No test for audit=NONE scenario to verify default audit behavior.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page and size) to validate correct paging and headers.
Introduce rate-limiting tests (e.g., 429) to ensure proper throttling behavior under load.
Add tests for caching behavior, validate ETag/Cache-Control headers and conditional requests (If-None-Match).
Add tests for 403 Forbidden to cover insufficient permission scenarios.
Add test for 500 Internal Server Error to ensure proper 500 handling in addition to 503.
Add regression test for audit=NONE to verify default audit behavior when audit parameter is absent or NONE.
Consider additional negative tests for edge parameter values (e.g., encoded input) to ensure robust parameter sanitization.
